## Fault Identification Time Evaluation

To evaluate the effectiveness of the proposed embedded diagnostic system, the fault identification time was experimentally measured and compared with conventional manual diagnosis over 10 trials.

### Manual Fault Identification Time

| Trial | Time (s) |
|-------|----------|
| 1 | 32 |
| 2 | 35 |
| 3 | 36 |
| 4 | 33 |
| 5 | 34 |
| 6 | 35 |
| 7 | 31 |
| 8 | 36 |
| 9 | 34 |
| 10 | 33 |

Average Manual Diagnosis Time

Average = (32 + 35 + 36 + 33 + 34 + 35 + 31 + 36 + 34 + 33) ÷ 10 = 33.9 s

---

### Proposed Embedded Diagnostic System

| Trial | Time (s) |
|-------|----------|
| 1 | 6 |
| 2 | 5 |
| 3 | 6 |
| 4 | 5 |
| 5 | 6 |
| 6 | 5 |
| 7 | 6 |
| 8 | 5 |
| 9 | 6 |
| 10 | 5 |

Average Proposed Embedded Diagnostic System Time

Average = (6 + 5 + 6 + 5 + 6 + 5 + 6 + 5 + 6 + 5) ÷ 10 = 5.5 s

---

### Percentage Reduction

Percentage Reduction = ((Manual Diagnosis Time − Proposed Embedded Diagnostic System Time) ÷ Manual Diagnosis Time) × 100

Percentage Reduction = ((33.9 − 5.5) ÷ 33.9) × 100

Percentage Reduction = (28.4 ÷ 33.9) × 100

Percentage Reduction = 83.8%

Approximately 84% reduction in fault identification time.

---

## Performance Comparison

| Method | Average Time |
|--------|--------------|
| Manual Diagnosis | 33.9 s |
| Proposed Embedded Diagnostic System | 5.5 s |

Result

The proposed embedded diagnostic system reduced the average fault identification time from 33.9 seconds to 5.5 seconds, achieving an approximately 84% reduction in fault diagnosis time through automated data acquisition, machine learning-based fault classification, and real-time visualization.
